    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>3 Executives Form A Global-Minded Shop</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By STUART ELLIOT</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Simon Anholt, Marc Cave and Joakim Jonason form Cave Anholt Jonason, advertising agency specializing in international clients (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Three top agency executives in Europe are leaving their posts to open a shop specializing in international clients.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Three top agency executives in Europe are leaving their posts to open a shop specializing in international clients.</p>
        <p>Cave Anholt Jonason in London is being opened by Simon Anholt, 38, who had been chairman at World Writers in London, a strategic consulting company; Marc Cave, 35, who had been executive vice president at the Lowe Group in London, part of the Interpublic Group of Companies; and Joakim Jonason, 42, who had been creative director at Paradiset DDB in Stockholm, part of the DDB Worldwide unit of the Omnicom Group. The three are all partners at the new shop.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
